<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2012/10/05/what-s-new-in-spring-integration-2-2-part-3-jpa-support">What&#39;s New in Spring Integration 2.2 (Part 3 – JPA Support)</a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon engineering"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/engineering">Engineering</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="https://gravatar.com/avatar/69270987b4535e921268c4bf8a800b2c?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<a class="author" href="/team/ghillert">Gunnar Hillert</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2012-10-05 16:36:00.0">October 5, 2012</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="488" href="/blog/2012/10/05/what-s-new-in-spring-integration-2-2-part-3-jpa-support#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><p>This is the third part in a series of blog posts highlighting some of the new features available in <a href="http://www.springsource.org/spring-integration/">Spring Integration</a> 2.2 following the recent release of <a href="http://www.springsource.org/node/3665">Release Candidate 1</a>. The <a href="http://blog.springsource.org/2012/09/24/whats-new-in-spring-integration-2-2-rc1-part-1-mongodb/">first part</a> described the new set of <a href="https://www.mongodb.org/">MongoDB</a> adapters. In <a href="http://blog.springsource.org/2012/09/26/whats-new-in-spring-integration-2-2-part-2-transaction-synchronization/">part two</a> we highlighted the new&nbsp;extended support for synchronizing non-transactional resources with transactions.</p>
<p>In this third part today, we would&nbsp;like to introduce the new <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Java_Persistence_API">Java Persistence API</a> (JPA) support that is provided starting with <em>Spring Integration 2.2</em>. The JPA module is persistence-provider-agnostic and has been tested using:<br></p>
</div>
</section>
<a class="blog-preview--readmore desktop-only" href="/blog/2012/10/05/what-s-new-in-spring-integration-2-2-part-3-jpa-support">
Read more...
</a>
